34   case class OpInfo(operand: Tree, operator: Ident, offset: Offset)

36   class ParensCounters {
37     private[this] var parCounts = new Array[Int](lastParen - firstParen)
38 
39     def count(tok: Token) = parCounts(tok - firstParen)
40     def change(tok: Token, delta: Int) = parCounts(tok - firstParen) += delta
41     def nonePositive: Boolean = parCounts forall (_ <= 0)
42   }
43 
44   @sharable object Location extends Enumeration {
45     val InParens, InBlock, InPattern, ElseWhere = Value
46   }

48   @sharable object ParamOwner extends Enumeration {
49     val Class, Type, TypeParam, Def = Value
50   }

52   private implicit class AddDeco(val buf: ListBuffer[Tree]) extends AnyVal {
53     def +++=(x: Tree) = x match {
54       case x: Thicket => buf ++= x.trees
55       case x => buf += x
56     }
57   }

59   /** The parse starting point depends on whether the source file is self-contained:
60    *  if not, the AST will be supplemented.
61    */
62   def parser(source: SourceFile)(implicit ctx: Context) =
63     if (source.isSelfContained) new ScriptParser(source)
64     else new Parser(source)
65 
66   abstract class ParserCommon(val source: SourceFile)(implicit ctx: Context) extends DotClass {
67 
68     val in: ScannerCommon
69 
70     /* ------------- POSITIONS ------------------------------------------- */
71 
72     /** Positions tree.
73      *  If `t` does not have a position yet, set its position to the given one.
74      */
75     def atPos[T <: Positioned](pos: Position)(t: T): T =
76       if (t.pos.isSourceDerived) t else t.withPos(pos)
77 
78     def atPos[T <: Positioned](start: Offset, point: Offset, end: Offset)(t: T): T =
79       atPos(Position(start, end, point))(t)
80 
81     /** If the last read offset is strictly greater than `start`, position tree
82      *  to position spanning from `start` to last read offset, with given point.
83      *  If the last offset is less than or equal to start, the tree `t` did not
84      *  consume any source for its construction. In this case, don't position it yet,
85      *  but wait for its position to be determined by `setChildPositions` when the
86      *  parent node is positioned.
87      */
88     def atPos[T <: Positioned](start: Offset, point: Offset)(t: T): T =
89       if (in.lastOffset > start) atPos(start, point, in.lastOffset)(t) else t
90 
91     def atPos[T <: Positioned](start: Offset)(t: T): T =
92       atPos(start, start)(t)
93 
94     def startOffset(t: Positioned): Int =
95       if (t.pos.exists) t.pos.start else in.offset
96 
97     def pointOffset(t: Positioned): Int =
98       if (t.pos.exists) t.pos.point else in.offset
99 
100     def endOffset(t: Positioned): Int =
101       if (t.pos.exists) t.pos.end else in.lastOffset
102 
103     def nameStart: Offset =
104       if (in.token == BACKQUOTED_IDENT) in.offset + 1 else in.offset
105 
106     def sourcePos(off: Int = in.offset): SourcePosition =
107       source atPos Position(off)
108 
109 
110     /* ------------- ERROR HANDLING ------------------------------------------- */
111     /** The offset where the last syntax error was reported, or if a skip to a
112       *  safepoint occurred afterwards, the offset of the safe point.
113       */
114     protected var lastErrorOffset : Int = -1
115 
116     /** Issue an error at given offset if beyond last error offset
117       *  and update lastErrorOffset.
118       */
119     def syntaxError(msg: => Message, offset: Int = in.offset): Unit =
120       if (offset > lastErrorOffset) {
121         val length = if (in.name != null) in.name.show.length else 0
122         syntaxError(msg, Position(offset, offset + length))
123         lastErrorOffset = in.offset
124       }
125 
126     /** Unconditionally issue an error at given position, without
127       *  updating lastErrorOffset.
128       */
129     def syntaxError(msg: => Message, pos: Position): Unit =
130       ctx.error(msg, source atPos pos)
131 
132   }

134   class Parser(source: SourceFile)(implicit ctx: Context) extends ParserCommon(source) {

136     val in: Scanner = new Scanner(source)
137 
138     val openParens = new ParensCounters
139 
140     /** This is the general parse entry point.
141      *  Overridden by ScriptParser
142      */
143     def parse(): Tree = {
144       val t = compilationUnit()
145       accept(EOF)
146       t
147     }

149 /* -------------- TOKEN CLASSES ------------------------------------------- */
150 
151     def isIdent = in.token == IDENTIFIER || in.token == BACKQUOTED_IDENT
152     def isIdent(name: Name) = in.token == IDENTIFIER && in.name == name
153     def isSimpleLiteral = simpleLiteralTokens contains in.token
154     def isLiteral = literalTokens contains in.token
155     def isNumericLit = numericLitTokens contains in.token
156     def isModifier = modifierTokens contains in.token
157     def isExprIntro = canStartExpressionTokens contains in.token
158     def isBindingIntro = canStartBindingTokens contains in.token
159     def isTemplateIntro = templateIntroTokens contains in.token
160     def isDclIntro = dclIntroTokens contains in.token
161     def isStatSeqEnd = in.token == RBRACE || in.token == EOF
162     def mustStartStat = mustStartStatTokens contains in.token
163 
164     def isDefIntro(allowedMods: BitSet) =
165       in.token == AT || (allowedMods contains in.token) || (defIntroTokens contains in.token)
166 
167     def isCaseIntro =
168       in.token == AT || (modifierTokensOrCase contains in.token)
169 
170     def isStatSep: Boolean =
171       in.token == NEWLINE || in.token == NEWLINES || in.token == SEMI
172 
173 /* ------------- ERROR HANDLING ------------------------------------------- */
174 
175     /** The offset of the last time when a statement on a new line was definitely
176      *  encountered in the current scope or an outer scope.
177      */
178     private[this] var lastStatOffset = -1
179 
180     def setLastStatOffset() =
181       if (mustStartStat && in.isAfterLineEnd())
182         lastStatOffset = in.offset
183 
184     /** Is offset1 less or equally indented than offset2?
185      *  This is the case if the characters between the preceding end-of-line and offset1
186      *  are a prefix of the characters between the preceding end-of-line and offset2.
187      */
188     def isLeqIndented(offset1: Int, offset2: Int): Boolean = {
189       def recur(idx1: Int, idx2: Int): Boolean =
190         idx1 == offset1 ||
191         idx2 < offset2 && source(idx1) == source(idx2) && recur(idx1 + 1, idx2 + 1)
192       recur(source.startOfLine(offset1), source.startOfLine(offset2))
193     }
194 
195     /** Skip on error to next safe point.
196      *  Safe points are:
197      *   - Closing braces, provided they match an opening brace before the error point.
198      *   - Closing parens and brackets, provided they match an opening parent or bracket
199      *     before the error point and there are no intervening other kinds of parens.
200      *   - Semicolons and newlines, provided there are no intervening braces.
201      *   - Definite statement starts on new lines, provided they are not more indented
202      *     than the last known statement start before the error point.
203      */
204     protected def skip(): Unit = {
205       val skippedParens = new ParensCounters
206       while (true) {
207         (in.token: @switch) match {
208           case EOF =>
209             return
210           case SEMI | NEWLINE | NEWLINES =>
211             if (skippedParens.count(LBRACE) == 0) return
212           case RBRACE =>
213             if (openParens.count(LBRACE) > 0 && skippedParens.count(LBRACE) == 0)
214               return
215             skippedParens.change(LBRACE, -1)
216           case RPAREN =>
217             if (openParens.count(LPAREN) > 0 && skippedParens.nonePositive)
218               return
219             skippedParens.change(LPAREN, -1)
220           case RBRACKET =>
221             if (openParens.count(LBRACKET) > 0 && skippedParens.nonePositive)
222               return
223             skippedParens.change(LBRACKET, -1)
224           case LBRACE =>
225             skippedParens.change(LBRACE, + 1)
226           case LPAREN =>
227             skippedParens.change(LPAREN, + 1)
228           case LBRACKET=>
229             skippedParens.change(LBRACKET, + 1)
230           case _ =>
231             if (mustStartStat &&
232                 in.isAfterLineEnd() &&
233                 isLeqIndented(in.offset, lastStatOffset max 0))
234               return
235         }
236         in.nextToken()
237       }
238     }
239 
240     def warning(msg: => Message, sourcePos: SourcePosition) =
241       ctx.warning(msg, sourcePos)
242 
243     def warning(msg: => Message, offset: Int = in.offset) =
244       ctx.warning(msg, source atPos Position(offset))
245 
246     def deprecationWarning(msg: => Message, offset: Int = in.offset) =
247       ctx.deprecationWarning(msg, source atPos Position(offset))
248 
249     /** Issue an error at current offset taht input is incomplete */
250     def incompleteInputError(msg: => Message) =
251       ctx.incompleteInputError(msg, source atPos Position(in.offset))
252 
253     /** If at end of file, issue an incompleteInputError.
254      *  Otherwise issue a syntax error and skip to next safe point.
255      */
256     def syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(msg: => Message) =
257       if (in.token == EOF) incompleteInputError(msg)
258       else {
259         syntaxError(msg)
260         skip()
261         lastErrorOffset = in.offset
262       } // DEBUG
263 
264     /** Consume one token of the specified type, or
265       * signal an error if it is not there.
266       *
267       * @return The offset at the start of the token to accept
268       */
269     def accept(token: Int): Int = {
270       val offset = in.offset
271       if (in.token != token) {
272         syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(ExpectedTokenButFound(token, in.token))
273       }
274       if (in.token == token) in.nextToken()
275       offset
276     }
277 
278     /** semi = nl {nl} | `;'
279      *  nl  = `\n' // where allowed
280      */
281     def acceptStatSep(): Unit = in.token match {
282       case NEWLINE | NEWLINES => in.nextToken()
283       case _                  => accept(SEMI)
284     }
285 
286     def acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd(altEnd: Token = EOF) =
287       if (!isStatSeqEnd)
288         in.token match {
289           case EOF =>
290           case `altEnd` =>
291           case NEWLINE | NEWLINES => in.nextToken()
292           case SEMI => in.nextToken()
293           case _ =>
294             in.nextToken() // needed to ensure progress; otherwise we might cycle forever
295             accept(SEMI)
296         }
297 
298     def errorTermTree    = atPos(in.offset) { Literal(Constant(null)) }
299 
300     private[this] var inFunReturnType = false
301     private def fromWithinReturnType[T](body: => T): T = {
302       val saved = inFunReturnType
303       try {
304         inFunReturnType = true
305         body
306       } finally inFunReturnType = saved
307     }
308 
309     /** A flag indicating we are parsing in the annotations of a primary
310      *  class constructor
311      */
312     private[this] var inClassConstrAnnots = false
313 
314     private def fromWithinClassConstr[T](body: => T): T = {
315       val saved = inClassConstrAnnots
316       inClassConstrAnnots = true
317       try body
318       finally inClassConstrAnnots = saved
319     }
320 
321     def migrationWarningOrError(msg: String, offset: Int = in.offset) =
322       if (in.isScala2Mode)
323         ctx.migrationWarning(msg, source atPos Position(offset))
324       else
325         syntaxError(msg, offset)

327 /* ---------- TREE CONSTRUCTION ------------------------------------------- */

329     /** Convert tree to formal parameter list
330     */
331     def convertToParams(tree: Tree): List[ValDef] = tree match {
332       case Parens(t)  => convertToParam(t) :: Nil
333       case Tuple(ts)  => ts map (convertToParam(_))
334       case t          => convertToParam(t) :: Nil
335     }
336 
337     /** Convert tree to formal parameter
338     */
339     def convertToParam(tree: Tree, mods: Modifiers = Modifiers(), expected: String = "formal parameter"): ValDef = tree match {
340       case Ident(name) =>
341         makeParameter(name.asTermName, TypeTree(), mods) withPos tree.pos
342       case Typed(Ident(name), tpt) =>
343         makeParameter(name.asTermName, tpt, mods) withPos tree.pos
344       case _ =>
345         syntaxError(s"not a legal $expected", tree.pos)
346         makeParameter(nme.ERROR, tree, mods)
347     }
348 
349     /** Convert (qual)ident to type identifier
350      */
351     def convertToTypeId(tree: Tree): Tree = tree match {
352       case id @ Ident(name) =>
353         cpy.Ident(id)(name.toTypeName)
354       case id @ Select(qual, name) =>
355         cpy.Select(id)(qual, name.toTypeName)
356       case _ =>
357         syntaxError(IdentifierExpected(tree.show), tree.pos)
358         tree
359     }
360 
361 /* --------------- PLACEHOLDERS ------------------------------------------- */
362 
363     /** The implicit parameters introduced by `_` in the current expression.
364      *  Parameters appear in reverse order.
365      */
366     var placeholderParams: List[ValDef] = Nil
367 
368     def checkNoEscapingPlaceholders[T](op: => T): T = {
369       val savedPlaceholderParams = placeholderParams
370       placeholderParams = Nil
371 
372       try op
373       finally {
374         placeholderParams match {
375           case vd :: _ => syntaxError(UnboundPlaceholderParameter(), vd.pos)
376           case _ =>
377         }
378         placeholderParams = savedPlaceholderParams
379       }
380     }
381 
382     def isWildcard(t: Tree): Boolean = t match {
383       case Ident(name1) => placeholderParams.nonEmpty && name1 == placeholderParams.head.name
384       case Typed(t1, _) => isWildcard(t1)
385       case Annotated(t1, _) => isWildcard(t1)
386       case Parens(t1) => isWildcard(t1)
387       case _ => false
388     }

402     def enclosed[T](tok: Token, body: => T): T = {
403       accept(tok)
404       openParens.change(tok, 1)
405       try body
406       finally {
407         accept(tok + 1)
408         openParens.change(tok, -1)
409       }
410     }
411 
412     def inParens[T](body: => T): T = enclosed(LPAREN, body)
413     def inBraces[T](body: => T): T = enclosed(LBRACE, body)
414     def inBrackets[T](body: => T): T = enclosed(LBRACKET, body)
415 
416     def inDefScopeBraces[T](body: => T): T = {
417       val saved = lastStatOffset
418       try inBraces(body)
419       finally lastStatOffset = saved
420     }
421 
422     /** part { `separator` part }
423      */
424     def tokenSeparated[T](separator: Int, part: () => T): List[T] = {
425       val ts = new ListBuffer[T] += part()
426       while (in.token == separator) {
427         in.nextToken()
428         ts += part()
429       }
430       ts.toList
431     }
432 
433     def commaSeparated[T](part: () => T): List[T] = tokenSeparated(COMMA, part)
434 
435     /** Is the token following the current one in `tokens`? */
436     def lookaheadIn(tokens: Token*): Boolean = {
437       val lookahead = in.lookaheadScanner
438       lookahead.nextToken()
439       tokens.contains(lookahead.token)
440     }

442 /* --------- OPERAND/OPERATOR STACK --------------------------------------- */
443 
444     var opStack: List[OpInfo] = Nil
445 
446     def checkAssoc(offset: Token, op1: Name, op2: Name, op2LeftAssoc: Boolean): Unit =
447       if (isLeftAssoc(op1) != op2LeftAssoc)
448         syntaxError(MixedLeftAndRightAssociativeOps(op1, op2, op2LeftAssoc), offset)
449 
450     def reduceStack(base: List[OpInfo], top: Tree, prec: Int, leftAssoc: Boolean, op2: Name): Tree = {
451       if (opStack != base && precedence(opStack.head.operator.name) == prec)
452         checkAssoc(opStack.head.offset, opStack.head.operator.name, op2, leftAssoc)
453       def recur(top: Tree): Tree = {
454         if (opStack == base) top
455         else {
456           val opInfo = opStack.head
457           val opPrec = precedence(opInfo.operator.name)
458           if (prec < opPrec || leftAssoc && prec == opPrec) {
459             opStack = opStack.tail
460             recur {
461               atPos(opInfo.operator.pos union opInfo.operand.pos union top.pos) {
462                 InfixOp(opInfo.operand, opInfo.operator, top)
463               }
464             }
465           }
466           else top
467         }
468       }
469       recur(top)
470     }
471 
472     /** operand { infixop operand} [postfixop],
473      *  respecting rules of associativity and precedence.
474      *  @param notAnOperator  a token that does not count as operator.
475      *  @param maybePostfix   postfix operators are allowed.
476      */
477     def infixOps(
478         first: Tree, canStartOperand: Token => Boolean, operand: () => Tree,
479         isType: Boolean = false,
480         isOperator: => Boolean = true,
481         maybePostfix: Boolean = false): Tree = {
482       val base = opStack
483       var top = first
484       while (isIdent && isOperator) {
485         val op = if (isType) typeIdent() else termIdent()
486         top = reduceStack(base, top, precedence(op.name), isLeftAssoc(op.name), op.name)
487         opStack = OpInfo(top, op, in.offset) :: opStack
488         newLineOptWhenFollowing(canStartOperand)
489         if (maybePostfix && !canStartOperand(in.token)) {
490           val topInfo = opStack.head
491           opStack = opStack.tail
492           val od = reduceStack(base, topInfo.operand, 0, true, in.name)
493           return atPos(startOffset(od), topInfo.offset) {
494             PostfixOp(od, topInfo.operator)
495           }
496         }
497         top = operand()
498       }
499       reduceStack(base, top, 0, true, in.name)
500     }
501 
502 /* -------- IDENTIFIERS AND LITERALS ------------------------------------------- */
503 
504     /** Accept identifier and return its name as a term name. */
505     def ident(): TermName =
506       if (isIdent) {
507         val name = in.name
508         in.nextToken()
509         name
510       } else {
511         syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(ExpectedTokenButFound(IDENTIFIER, in.token))
512         nme.ERROR
513       }
514 
515     /** Accept identifier and return Ident with its name as a term name. */
516     def termIdent(): Ident = atPos(in.offset) {
517       makeIdent(in.token, ident())
518     }
519 
520     /** Accept identifier and return Ident with its name as a type name. */
521     def typeIdent(): Ident = atPos(in.offset) {
522       makeIdent(in.token, ident().toTypeName)
523     }
524 
525     private def makeIdent(tok: Token, name: Name) =
526       if (tok == BACKQUOTED_IDENT) BackquotedIdent(name)
527       else Ident(name)
528 
529     def wildcardIdent(): Ident =
530       atPos(accept(USCORE)) { Ident(nme.WILDCARD) }
531 
532     def termIdentOrWildcard(): Ident =
533       if (in.token == USCORE) wildcardIdent() else termIdent()
534 
535     /** Accept identifier acting as a selector on given tree `t`. */
536     def selector(t: Tree): Tree =
537       atPos(startOffset(t), in.offset) { Select(t, ident()) }
538 
539     /** Selectors ::= id { `.' id }
540      *
541      *  Accept `.' separated identifiers acting as a selectors on given tree `t`.
542      *  @param finish   An alternative parse in case the next token is not an identifier.
543      *                  If the alternative does not apply, its tree argument is returned unchanged.
544      */
545     def selectors(t: Tree, finish: Tree => Tree): Tree = {
546       val t1 = finish(t)
547       if (t1 ne t) t1 else dotSelectors(selector(t), finish)
548     }
549 
550     /** DotSelectors ::= { `.' id }
551      *
552      *  Accept `.' separated identifiers acting as a selectors on given tree `t`.
553      *  @param finish   An alternative parse in case the token following a `.' is not an identifier.
554      *                  If the alternative does not apply, its tree argument is returned unchanged.
555      */
556      def dotSelectors(t: Tree, finish: Tree => Tree = id) =
557       if (in.token == DOT) { in.nextToken(); selectors(t, finish) }
558       else t
559 
560     private val id: Tree => Tree = x => x
561 
562     /** Path       ::= StableId
563      *              |  [id `.'] this
564      *
565      *  @param thisOK   If true, the path can end with the keyword `this`.
566      *                  If false, another selection is required after the `this`.
567      *  @param finish   An alternative parse in case the token following a `.' is not an identifier.
568      *                  If the alternative does not apply, its tree argument is returned unchanged.
569      */
570     def path(thisOK: Boolean, finish: Tree => Tree = id): Tree = {
571       val start = in.offset
572       def handleThis(qual: Ident) = {
573         in.nextToken()
574         val t = atPos(start) { This(qual) }
575         if (!thisOK && in.token != DOT) syntaxError(DanglingThisInPath(), t.pos)
576         dotSelectors(t, finish)
577       }
578       def handleSuper(qual: Ident) = {
579         in.nextToken()
580         val mix = mixinQualifierOpt()
581         val t = atPos(start) { Super(This(qual), mix) }
582         accept(DOT)
583         dotSelectors(selector(t), finish)
584       }
585       if (in.token == THIS) handleThis(EmptyTypeIdent)
586       else if (in.token == SUPER) handleSuper(EmptyTypeIdent)
587       else {
588         val t = termIdent()
589         if (in.token == DOT) {
590           def qual = cpy.Ident(t)(t.name.toTypeName)
591           in.nextToken()
592           if (in.token == THIS) handleThis(qual)
593           else if (in.token == SUPER) handleSuper(qual)
594           else selectors(t, finish)
595         }
596         else t
597       }
598     }
599 
600     /** MixinQualifier ::= `[' id `]'
601     */
602     def mixinQualifierOpt(): Ident =
603       if (in.token == LBRACKET) inBrackets(atPos(in.offset) { typeIdent() })
604       else EmptyTypeIdent
605 
606     /** StableId ::= id
607      *            |  Path `.' id
608      *            |  [id '.'] super [`[' id `]']`.' id
609      */
610     def stableId(): Tree =
611       path(thisOK = false)
612 
613     /** QualId ::= id {`.' id}
614     */
615     def qualId(): Tree =
616       dotSelectors(termIdent())
617 
618     /** SimpleExpr    ::= literal
619      *                  | symbol
620      *                  | null
621      *  @param negOffset   The offset of a preceding `-' sign, if any.
622      *                     If the literal is not negated, negOffset = in.offset.
623      */
624     def literal(negOffset: Int = in.offset, inPattern: Boolean = false): Tree = {
625       def finish(value: Any): Tree = {
626         val t = atPos(negOffset) { Literal(Constant(value)) }
627         in.nextToken()
628         t
629       }
630       val isNegated = negOffset < in.offset
631       atPos(negOffset) {
632         if (in.token == SYMBOLLIT) atPos(in.skipToken()) { SymbolLit(in.strVal) }
633         else if (in.token == INTERPOLATIONID) interpolatedString(inPattern)
634         else finish(in.token match {
635           case CHARLIT                => in.charVal
636           case INTLIT                 => in.intVal(isNegated).toInt
637           case LONGLIT                => in.intVal(isNegated)
638           case FLOATLIT               => in.floatVal(isNegated).toFloat
639           case DOUBLELIT              => in.floatVal(isNegated)
640           case STRINGLIT | STRINGPART => in.strVal
641           case TRUE                   => true
642           case FALSE                  => false
643           case NULL                   => null
644           case _                      =>
645             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(IllegalLiteral())
646             null
647         })
648       }
649     }
650 
651     private def interpolatedString(inPattern: Boolean = false): Tree = atPos(in.offset) {
652       val segmentBuf = new ListBuffer[Tree]
653       val interpolator = in.name
654       in.nextToken()
655       while (in.token == STRINGPART) {
656         segmentBuf += Thicket(
657             literal(inPattern = inPattern),
658             atPos(in.offset) {
659               if (in.token == IDENTIFIER)
660                 termIdent()
661               else if (in.token == USCORE && inPattern) {
662                 in.nextToken()
663                 Ident(nme.WILDCARD)
664               }
665               else if (in.token == THIS) {
666                 in.nextToken()
667                 This(EmptyTypeIdent)
668               }
669               else if (in.token == LBRACE)
670                 if (inPattern) Block(Nil, inBraces(pattern()))
671                 else expr()
672               else {
673                 ctx.error(InterpolatedStringError(), source atPos Position(in.offset))
674                 EmptyTree
675               }
676             })
677       }
678       if (in.token == STRINGLIT) segmentBuf += literal(inPattern = inPattern)
679       InterpolatedString(interpolator, segmentBuf.toList)
680     }
681 
682 /* ------------- NEW LINES ------------------------------------------------- */
683 
684     def newLineOpt(): Unit = {
685       if (in.token == NEWLINE) in.nextToken()
686     }
687 
688     def newLinesOpt(): Unit = {
689       if (in.token == NEWLINE || in.token == NEWLINES)
690         in.nextToken()
691     }
692 
693     def newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(token: Int): Unit = {
694       // note: next is defined here because current == NEWLINE
695       if (in.token == NEWLINE && in.next.token == token) newLineOpt()
696     }
697 
698     def newLineOptWhenFollowing(p: Int => Boolean): Unit = {
699       // note: next is defined here because current == NEWLINE
700       if (in.token == NEWLINE && p(in.next.token)) newLineOpt()
701     }
702 
703 /* ------------- TYPES ------------------------------------------------------ */
704     /** Same as [[typ]], but if this results in a wildcard it emits a syntax error and
705      *  returns a tree for type `Any` instead.
706      */
707     def toplevelTyp(): Tree = {
708       val t = typ()
709       findWildcardType(t) match {
710         case Some(wildcardPos) =>
711           syntaxError(UnboundWildcardType(), wildcardPos)
712           scalaAny
713         case None => t
714       }
715     }
716 
717     /** Type        ::=  [`implicit'] FunArgTypes `=>' Type
718      *                |  HkTypeParamClause `->' Type
719      *                |  InfixType
720      *  FunArgTypes ::=  InfixType
721      *                |  `(' [ FunArgType {`,' FunArgType } ] `)'
722      *                |  '(' TypedFunParam {',' TypedFunParam } ')'
723      */
724     def typ(): Tree = {
725       val start = in.offset
726       val isImplicit = in.token == IMPLICIT
727       if (isImplicit) in.nextToken()
728       def functionRest(params: List[Tree]): Tree =
729         atPos(start, accept(ARROW)) {
730           val t = typ()
731           if (isImplicit) new ImplicitFunction(params, t) else Function(params, t)
732         }
733       def funArgTypesRest(first: Tree, following: () => Tree) = {
734         val buf = new ListBuffer[Tree] += first
735         while (in.token == COMMA) {
736           in.nextToken()
737           buf += following()
738         }
739         buf.toList
740       }
741       var isValParamList = false
742 
743       val t =
744         if (in.token == LPAREN) {
745           in.nextToken()
746           if (in.token == RPAREN) {
747             in.nextToken()
748             functionRest(Nil)
749           }
750           else {
751             openParens.change(LPAREN, 1)
752             val paramStart = in.offset
753             val ts = funArgType() match {
754               case Ident(name) if name != tpnme.WILDCARD && in.token == COLON =>
755                 isValParamList = true
756                 funArgTypesRest(
757                     typedFunParam(paramStart, name.toTermName),
758                     () => typedFunParam(in.offset, ident()))
759               case t =>
760                 funArgTypesRest(t, funArgType)
761             }
762             openParens.change(LPAREN, -1)
763             accept(RPAREN)
764             if (isImplicit || isValParamList || in.token == ARROW) functionRest(ts)
765             else {
766               for (t <- ts)
767                 if (t.isInstanceOf[ByNameTypeTree])
768                   syntaxError(ByNameParameterNotSupported())
769               val tuple = atPos(start) { makeTupleOrParens(ts) }
770               infixTypeRest(
771                 refinedTypeRest(
772                   withTypeRest(
773                     annotTypeRest(
774                       simpleTypeRest(tuple)))))
775             }
776           }
777         }
778         else if (in.token == LBRACKET) {
779           val start = in.offset
780           val tparams = typeParamClause(ParamOwner.TypeParam)
781           if (in.token == ARROW)
782             atPos(start, in.skipToken())(LambdaTypeTree(tparams, typ()))
783           else { accept(ARROW); typ() }
784         }
785         else infixType()
786 
787       in.token match {
788         case ARROW => functionRest(t :: Nil)
789         case FORSOME => syntaxError(ExistentialTypesNoLongerSupported()); t
790         case _ =>
791           if (isImplicit && !t.isInstanceOf[ImplicitFunction])
792             syntaxError("Types with implicit keyword can only be function types", Position(start, start + nme.IMPLICITkw.asSimpleName.length))
793           t
794       }
795     }
796 
797     /** TypedFunParam   ::= id ':' Type */
798     def typedFunParam(start: Offset, name: TermName): Tree = atPos(start) {
799       accept(COLON)
800       makeParameter(name, typ(), Modifiers(Param))
801     }
802 
803     /** InfixType ::= RefinedType {id [nl] refinedType}
804      */
805     def infixType(): Tree = infixTypeRest(refinedType())
806 
807     /** Is current ident a `*`, and is it followed by a `)` or `,`? */
808     def isPostfixStar: Boolean =
809       in.name == nme.raw.STAR && lookaheadIn(RPAREN, COMMA)
810 
811     def infixTypeRest(t: Tree): Tree =
812       infixOps(t, canStartTypeTokens, refinedType, isType = true, isOperator = !isPostfixStar)
813 
814     /** RefinedType        ::=  WithType {Annotation | [nl] Refinement}
815      */
816     val refinedType: () => Tree = () => refinedTypeRest(withType())
817 
818     def refinedTypeRest(t: Tree): Tree = {
819       newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
820       if (in.token == LBRACE) refinedTypeRest(atPos(startOffset(t)) { RefinedTypeTree(t, refinement()) })
821       else t
822     }
823 
824     /** WithType ::= AnnotType {`with' AnnotType}    (deprecated)
825      */
826     def withType(): Tree = withTypeRest(annotType())
827 
828     def withTypeRest(t: Tree): Tree =
829       if (in.token == WITH) {
830         if (ctx.settings.strict.value)
831           deprecationWarning(DeprecatedWithOperator())
832         in.nextToken()
833         AndTypeTree(t, withType())
834       }
835       else t
836 
837     /** AnnotType ::= SimpleType {Annotation}
838      */
839     def annotType(): Tree = annotTypeRest(simpleType())
840 
841     def annotTypeRest(t: Tree): Tree =
842       if (in.token == AT) annotTypeRest(atPos(startOffset(t)) { Annotated(t, annot()) })
843       else t
844 
845     /** SimpleType       ::=  SimpleType TypeArgs
846      *                     |  SimpleType `#' id
847      *                     |  StableId
848      *                     |  ['~'] StableId
849      *                     |  Path `.' type
850      *                     |  `(' ArgTypes `)'
851      *                     |  `_' TypeBounds
852      *                     |  Refinement
853      *                     |  Literal
854      */
855     def simpleType(): Tree = simpleTypeRest {
856       if (in.token == LPAREN)
857         atPos(in.offset) {
858           makeTupleOrParens(inParens(argTypes(namedOK = false, wildOK = true)))
859         }
860       else if (in.token == LBRACE)
861         atPos(in.offset) { RefinedTypeTree(EmptyTree, refinement()) }
862       else if (isSimpleLiteral) { SingletonTypeTree(literal()) }
863       else if (in.token == USCORE) {
864         val start = in.skipToken()
865         typeBounds().withPos(Position(start, in.lastOffset, start))
866       }
867       else if (isIdent(nme.raw.TILDE) && lookaheadIn(IDENTIFIER, BACKQUOTED_IDENT))
868         atPos(in.offset) { PrefixOp(typeIdent(), path(thisOK = true)) }
869       else path(thisOK = false, handleSingletonType) match {
870         case r @ SingletonTypeTree(_) => r
871         case r => convertToTypeId(r)
872       }
873     }
874 
875     val handleSingletonType: Tree => Tree = t =>
876       if (in.token == TYPE) {
877         in.nextToken()
878         atPos(startOffset(t)) { SingletonTypeTree(t) }
879       } else t
880 
881     private def simpleTypeRest(t: Tree): Tree = in.token match {
882       case HASH => simpleTypeRest(typeProjection(t))
883       case LBRACKET => simpleTypeRest(atPos(startOffset(t)) {
884         AppliedTypeTree(t, typeArgs(namedOK = false, wildOK = true)) })
885       case _ => t
886     }
887 
888     private def typeProjection(t: Tree): Tree = {
889       accept(HASH)
890       val id = typeIdent()
891       atPos(startOffset(t), startOffset(id)) { Select(t, id.name) }
892     }
893 
894     /** NamedTypeArg      ::=  id `=' Type
895      */
896     val namedTypeArg = () => {
897       val name = ident()
898       accept(EQUALS)
899       NamedArg(name.toTypeName, typ())
900     }
901 
902     /**   ArgTypes          ::=  Type {`,' Type}
903      *                        |  NamedTypeArg {`,' NamedTypeArg}
904      */
905     def argTypes(namedOK: Boolean, wildOK: Boolean) = {
906       def otherArgs(first: Tree, arg: () => Tree): List[Tree] = {
907         val rest =
908           if (in.token == COMMA) {
909             in.nextToken()
910             commaSeparated(arg)
911           }
912           else Nil
913         first :: rest
914       }
915       def typParser() = if (wildOK) typ() else toplevelTyp()
916       if (namedOK && in.token == IDENTIFIER)
917         typParser() match {
918           case Ident(name) if in.token == EQUALS =>
919             in.nextToken()
920             otherArgs(NamedArg(name, typ()), namedTypeArg)
921           case firstArg =>
922             otherArgs(firstArg, () => typ())
923         }
924       else commaSeparated(() => typParser())
925     }
926 
927     /** FunArgType ::=  Type | `=>' Type
928      */
929     val funArgType = () =>
930       if (in.token == ARROW) atPos(in.skipToken()) { ByNameTypeTree(typ()) }
931       else typ()
932 
933     /** ParamType ::= [`=>'] ParamValueType
934      */
935     def paramType(): Tree =
936       if (in.token == ARROW) atPos(in.skipToken()) { ByNameTypeTree(paramValueType()) }
937       else paramValueType()
938 
939     /** ParamValueType ::= Type [`*']
940      */
941     def paramValueType(): Tree = {
942       val t = toplevelTyp()
943       if (isIdent(nme.raw.STAR)) {
944         in.nextToken()
945         atPos(startOffset(t)) { PostfixOp(t, Ident(tpnme.raw.STAR)) }
946       } else t
947     }
948 
949     /** TypeArgs      ::= `[' Type {`,' Type} `]'
950      *  NamedTypeArgs ::= `[' NamedTypeArg {`,' NamedTypeArg} `]'
951      */
952     def typeArgs(namedOK: Boolean, wildOK: Boolean): List[Tree] = inBrackets(argTypes(namedOK, wildOK))
953 
954     /** Refinement ::= `{' RefineStatSeq `}'
955      */
956     def refinement(): List[Tree] = inBraces(refineStatSeq())
957 
958     /** TypeBounds ::= [`>:' Type] [`<:' Type]
959      */
960     def typeBounds(): TypeBoundsTree =
961       atPos(in.offset) { TypeBoundsTree(bound(SUPERTYPE), bound(SUBTYPE)) }
962 
963     private def bound(tok: Int): Tree =
964       if (in.token == tok) { in.nextToken(); toplevelTyp() }
965       else EmptyTree
966 
967     /** TypeParamBounds   ::=  TypeBounds {`<%' Type} {`:' Type}
968      */
969     def typeParamBounds(pname: TypeName): Tree = {
970       val t = typeBounds()
971       val cbs = contextBounds(pname)
972       if (cbs.isEmpty) t
973       else atPos((t.pos union cbs.head.pos).start) { ContextBounds(t, cbs) }
974     }
975 
976     def contextBounds(pname: TypeName): List[Tree] = in.token match {
977       case COLON =>
978         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
979           AppliedTypeTree(toplevelTyp(), Ident(pname))
980         } :: contextBounds(pname)
981       case VIEWBOUND =>
982         deprecationWarning("view bounds `<%' are deprecated, use a context bound `:' instead")
983         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
984           Function(Ident(pname) :: Nil, toplevelTyp())
985         } :: contextBounds(pname)
986       case _ =>
987         Nil
988     }
989 
990     def typedOpt(): Tree =
991       if (in.token == COLON) { in.nextToken(); toplevelTyp() }
992       else TypeTree()
993 
994     def typeDependingOn(location: Location.Value): Tree =
995       if (location == Location.InParens) typ()
996       else if (location == Location.InPattern) refinedType()
997       else infixType()
998 
999     /** Checks whether `t` is a wildcard type.
1000      *  If it is, returns the [[Position]] where the wildcard occurs.
1001      */
1002     @tailrec
1003     private final def findWildcardType(t: Tree): Option[Position] = t match {
1004       case TypeBoundsTree(_, _) => Some(t.pos)
1005       case Parens(t1) => findWildcardType(t1)
1006       case Annotated(t1, _) => findWildcardType(t1)
1007       case _ => None
1008     }
1009 
1010 /* ----------- EXPRESSIONS ------------------------------------------------ */
1011 
1012     /** EqualsExpr ::= `=' Expr
1013      */
1014     def equalsExpr(): Tree = {
1015       accept(EQUALS)
1016       expr()
1017     }
1018 
1019     def condExpr(altToken: Token): Tree = {
1020       if (in.token == LPAREN) {
1021         val t = atPos(in.offset) { Parens(inParens(exprInParens())) }
1022         if (in.token == altToken) in.nextToken()
1023         t
1024       } else {
1025         val t = expr()
1026         accept(altToken)
1027         t
1028       }
1029     }
1030 
1031     /** Expr              ::=  [`implicit'] FunParams `=>' Expr
1032      *                      |  Expr1
1033      *  FunParams         ::=  Bindings
1034      *                      |  id
1035      *                      |  `_'
1036      *  ExprInParens      ::=  PostfixExpr `:' Type
1037      *                      |  Expr
1038      *  BlockResult       ::=  [`implicit'] FunParams `=>' Block
1039      *                      |  Expr1
1040      *  Expr1             ::=  `if' `(' Expr `)' {nl} Expr [[semi] else Expr]
1041      *                      |  `if' Expr `then' Expr [[semi] else Expr]
1042      *                      |  `while' `(' Expr `)' {nl} Expr
1043      *                      |  `while' Expr `do' Expr
1044      *                      |  `do' Expr [semi] `while' Expr
1045      *                      |  `try' Expr Catches [`finally' Expr]
1046      *                      |  `try' Expr [`finally' Expr]
1047      *                      |  `throw' Expr
1048      *                      |  `return' [Expr]
1049      *                      |  ForExpr
1050      *                      |  [SimpleExpr `.'] id `=' Expr
1051      *                      |  SimpleExpr1 ArgumentExprs `=' Expr
1052      *                      |  PostfixExpr [Ascription]
1053      *                      |  PostfixExpr `match' `{' CaseClauses `}'
1054      *  Bindings          ::= `(' [Binding {`,' Binding}] `)'
1055      *  Binding           ::= (id | `_') [`:' Type]
1056      *  Ascription        ::= `:' CompoundType
1057      *                      | `:' Annotation {Annotation}
1058      *                      | `:' `_' `*'
1059      */
1060     val exprInParens = () => expr(Location.InParens)
1061 
1062     def expr(): Tree = expr(Location.ElseWhere)
1063 
1064     def expr(location: Location.Value): Tree = {
1065       val start = in.offset
1066       if (in.token == IMPLICIT)
1067         implicitClosure(start, location, implicitMods())
1068       else {
1069         val saved = placeholderParams
1070         placeholderParams = Nil
1071 
1072         def wrapPlaceholders(t: Tree) = try
1073           if (placeholderParams.isEmpty) t
1074           else new WildcardFunction(placeholderParams.reverse, t)
1075         finally placeholderParams = saved
1076 
1077         val t = expr1(location)
1078         if (in.token == ARROW) {
1079           placeholderParams = Nil // don't interpret `_' to the left of `=>` as placeholder
1080           wrapPlaceholders(closureRest(start, location, convertToParams(t)))
1081         }
1082         else if (isWildcard(t)) {
1083           placeholderParams = placeholderParams ::: saved
1084           t
1085         }
1086         else wrapPlaceholders(t)
1087       }
1088     }
1089 
1090     def expr1(location: Location.Value = Location.ElseWhere): Tree = in.token match {
1091       case IF =>
1092         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
1093           val cond = condExpr(THEN)
1094           newLinesOpt()
1095           val thenp = expr()
1096           val elsep = if (in.token == ELSE) { in.nextToken(); expr() }
1097                       else EmptyTree
1098           If(cond, thenp, elsep)
1099         }
1100       case WHILE =>
1101         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
1102           val cond = condExpr(DO)
1103           newLinesOpt()
1104           val body = expr()
1105           WhileDo(cond, body)
1106         }
1107       case DO =>
1108         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
1109           val body = expr()
1110           if (isStatSep) in.nextToken()
1111           accept(WHILE)
1112           val cond = expr()
1113           DoWhile(body, cond)
1114         }
1115       case TRY =>
1116         val tryOffset = in.offset
1117         atPos(in.skipToken()) {
1118           val body = expr()
1119           val (handler, handlerStart) =
1120             if (in.token == CATCH) {
1121               val pos = in.offset
1122               in.nextToken()
1123               (expr(), pos)
1124             } else (EmptyTree, -1)
1125 
1126           handler match {
1127             case Block(Nil, EmptyTree) =>
1128               assert(handlerStart != -1)
1129               syntaxError(
1130                 EmptyCatchBlock(body),
1131                 Position(handlerStart, endOffset(handler))
1132               )
1133             case _ =>
1134           }
1135 
1136           val finalizer =
1137             if (in.token == FINALLY) { accept(FINALLY); expr() }
1138             else {
1139               if (handler.isEmpty) warning(
1140                 EmptyCatchAndFinallyBlock(body),
1141                 source atPos Position(tryOffset, endOffset(body))
1142               )
1143               EmptyTree
1144             }
1145           ParsedTry(body, handler, finalizer)
1146         }
1147       case THROW =>
1148         atPos(in.skipToken()) { Throw(expr()) }
1149       case RETURN =>
1150         atPos(in.skipToken()) { Return(if (isExprIntro) expr() else EmptyTree, EmptyTree) }
1151       case FOR =>
1152         forExpr()
1153       case _ =>
1154         expr1Rest(postfixExpr(), location)
1155     }
1156 
1157     def expr1Rest(t: Tree, location: Location.Value) = in.token match {
1158       case EQUALS =>
1159          t match {
1160            case Ident(_) | Select(_, _) | Apply(_, _) =>
1161              atPos(startOffset(t), in.skipToken()) { Assign(t, expr()) }
1162            case _ =>
1163              t
1164          }
1165       case COLON =>
1166         ascription(t, location)
1167       case MATCH =>
1168         atPos(startOffset(t), in.skipToken()) {
1169           inBraces(Match(t, caseClauses()))
1170         }
1171       case _ =>
1172         t
1173     }
1174 
1175     def ascription(t: Tree, location: Location.Value) = atPos(startOffset(t)) {
1176       in.skipToken()
1177       in.token match {
1178         case USCORE =>
1179           val uscoreStart = in.skipToken()
1180           if (isIdent(nme.raw.STAR)) {
1181             in.nextToken()
1182             if (in.token != RPAREN) syntaxError(SeqWildcardPatternPos(), uscoreStart)
1183             Typed(t, atPos(uscoreStart) { Ident(tpnme.WILDCARD_STAR) })
1184           } else {
1185             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(IncorrectRepeatedParameterSyntax())
1186             t
1187           }
1188         case AT if location != Location.InPattern =>
1189           (t /: annotations())(Annotated)
1190         case _ =>
1191           val tpt = typeDependingOn(location)
1192           if (isWildcard(t) && location != Location.InPattern) {
1193             val vd :: rest = placeholderParams
1194             placeholderParams =
1195               cpy.ValDef(vd)(tpt = tpt).withPos(vd.pos union tpt.pos) :: rest
1196           }
1197           Typed(t, tpt)
1198       }
1199     }
1200 
1201     /** FunParams         ::=  Bindings
1202      *                     |   id
1203      *                     |   `_'
1204      *  Bindings          ::=  `(' [Binding {`,' Binding}] `)'
1205      */
1206     def funParams(mods: Modifiers, location: Location.Value): List[Tree] =
1207       if (in.token == LPAREN)
1208         inParens(if (in.token == RPAREN) Nil else commaSeparated(() => binding(mods)))
1209       else {
1210         val start = in.offset
1211         val name = bindingName()
1212         val t =
1213           if (in.token == COLON && location == Location.InBlock) {
1214             if (ctx.settings.strict.value)
1215                 // Don't error in non-strict mode, as the alternative syntax "implicit (x: T) => ... "
1216                 // is not supported by Scala2.x
1217               migrationWarningOrError(s"This syntax is no longer supported; parameter needs to be enclosed in (...)")
1218             in.nextToken()
1219             val t = infixType()
1220             if (false && in.isScala2Mode) {
1221               patch(source, Position(start), "(")
1222               patch(source, Position(in.lastOffset), ")")
1223             }
1224             t
1225           }
1226           else TypeTree()
1227         (atPos(start) { makeParameter(name, t, mods) }) :: Nil
1228       }
1229 
1230     /**  Binding           ::= (id | `_') [`:' Type]
1231      */
1232     def binding(mods: Modifiers): Tree =
1233       atPos(in.offset) { makeParameter(bindingName(), typedOpt(), mods) }
1234 
1235     def bindingName(): TermName =
1236       if (in.token == USCORE) {
1237         in.nextToken()
1238         WildcardParamName.fresh()
1239       }
1240       else ident()
1241 
1242     /** Expr         ::= implicit id `=>' Expr
1243      *  BlockResult  ::= implicit id [`:' InfixType] `=>' Block // Scala2 only
1244      */
1245     def implicitClosure(start: Int, location: Location.Value, implicitMods: Modifiers): Tree =
1246       closureRest(start, location, funParams(implicitMods, location))
1247 
1248     def closureRest(start: Int, location: Location.Value, params: List[Tree]): Tree =
1249       atPos(start, in.offset) {
1250         accept(ARROW)
1251         Function(params, if (location == Location.InBlock) block() else expr())
1252       }
1253 
1254     /** PostfixExpr   ::= InfixExpr [id [nl]]
1255      *  InfixExpr     ::= PrefixExpr
1256      *                  | InfixExpr id [nl] InfixExpr
1257      */
1258     def postfixExpr(): Tree =
1259       infixOps(prefixExpr(), canStartExpressionTokens, prefixExpr, maybePostfix = true)
1260 
1261     /** PrefixExpr   ::= [`-' | `+' | `~' | `!'] SimpleExpr
1262     */
1263     val prefixExpr = () =>
1264       if (isIdent && nme.raw.isUnary(in.name)) {
1265         val start = in.offset
1266         val op = termIdent()
1267         if (op.name == nme.raw.MINUS && isNumericLit)
1268           simpleExprRest(literal(start), canApply = true)
1269         else
1270           atPos(start) { PrefixOp(op, simpleExpr()) }
1271       }
1272       else simpleExpr()
1273 
1274     /** SimpleExpr    ::= new Template
1275      *                 |  BlockExpr
1276      *                 |  '{ BlockExprContents }
1277      *                 |  '( ExprsInParens )
1278      *                 |  '[ Type ]
1279      *                 |  SimpleExpr1 [`_']
1280      *  SimpleExpr1   ::= literal
1281      *                 |  xmlLiteral
1282      *                 |  Path
1283      *                 |  `(' [ExprsInParens] `)'
1284      *                 |  SimpleExpr `.' id
1285      *                 |  SimpleExpr (TypeArgs | NamedTypeArgs)
1286      *                 |  SimpleExpr1 ArgumentExprs
1287      */
1288     def simpleExpr(): Tree = {
1289       var canApply = true
1290       val t = in.token match {
1291         case XMLSTART =>
1292           xmlLiteral()
1293         case IDENTIFIER | BACKQUOTED_IDENT | THIS | SUPER =>
1294           path(thisOK = true)
1295         case USCORE =>
1296           val start = in.skipToken()
1297           val pname = WildcardParamName.fresh()
1298           val param = ValDef(pname, TypeTree(), EmptyTree).withFlags(SyntheticTermParam)
1299             .withPos(Position(start))
1300           placeholderParams = param :: placeholderParams
1301           atPos(start) { Ident(pname) }
1302         case LPAREN =>
1303           atPos(in.offset) { makeTupleOrParens(inParens(exprsInParensOpt())) }
1304         case LBRACE =>
1305           canApply = false
1306           blockExpr()
1307         case QPAREN =>
1308           in.token = LPAREN
1309           atPos(in.offset)(Quote(simpleExpr()))
1310         case QBRACE =>
1311           in.token = LBRACE
1312           atPos(in.offset)(Quote(simpleExpr()))
1313         case QBRACKET =>
1314           in.token = LBRACKET
1315           atPos(in.offset)(Quote(inBrackets(typ())))
1316         case NEW =>
1317           canApply = false
1318           val start = in.skipToken()
1319           val (impl, missingBody) = template(emptyConstructor)
1320           impl.parents match {
1321             case parent :: Nil if missingBody =>
1322               if (parent.isType) ensureApplied(wrapNew(parent)) else parent
1323             case _ =>
1324               New(impl.withPos(Position(start, in.lastOffset)))
1325           }
1326         case _ =>
1327           if (isLiteral) literal()
1328           else {
1329             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(IllegalStartSimpleExpr(tokenString(in.token)))
1330             errorTermTree
1331           }
1332       }
1333       simpleExprRest(t, canApply)
1334     }
1335 
1336     def simpleExprRest(t: Tree, canApply: Boolean = true): Tree = {
1337       if (canApply) newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
1338       in.token match {
1339         case DOT =>
1340           in.nextToken()
1341           simpleExprRest(selector(t), canApply = true)
1342         case LBRACKET =>
1343           val tapp = atPos(startOffset(t), in.offset) { TypeApply(t, typeArgs(namedOK = true, wildOK = false)) }
1344           simpleExprRest(tapp, canApply = true)
1345         case LPAREN | LBRACE if canApply =>
1346           val app = atPos(startOffset(t), in.offset) { Apply(t, argumentExprs()) }
1347           simpleExprRest(app, canApply = true)
1348         case USCORE =>
1349           atPos(startOffset(t), in.skipToken()) { PostfixOp(t, Ident(nme.WILDCARD)) }
1350         case _ =>
1351           t
1352       }
1353     }
1354 
1355     /**   ExprsInParens     ::=  ExprInParens {`,' ExprInParens}
1356      */
1357     def exprsInParensOpt(): List[Tree] =
1358       if (in.token == RPAREN) Nil else commaSeparated(exprInParens)
1359 
1360     /** ParArgumentExprs ::= `(' [ExprsInParens] `)'
1361      *                    |  `(' [ExprsInParens `,'] PostfixExpr `:' `_' `*' ')'
1362      */
1363     def parArgumentExprs(): List[Tree] =
1364       inParens(if (in.token == RPAREN) Nil else commaSeparated(argumentExpr))
1365 
1366     /** ArgumentExprs ::= ParArgumentExprs
1367      *                 |  [nl] BlockExpr
1368      */
1369     def argumentExprs(): List[Tree] =
1370       if (in.token == LBRACE) blockExpr() :: Nil else parArgumentExprs()
1371 
1372     val argumentExpr = () => exprInParens() match {
1373       case arg @ Assign(Ident(id), rhs) => cpy.NamedArg(arg)(id, rhs)
1374       case arg => arg
1375     }
1376 
1377 
1378     /** ArgumentExprss ::= {ArgumentExprs}
1379      */
1380     def argumentExprss(fn: Tree): Tree = {
1381       newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
1382       if (in.token == LPAREN || in.token == LBRACE) argumentExprss(Apply(fn, argumentExprs()))
1383       else fn
1384     }
1385 
1386     /** ParArgumentExprss ::= {ParArgumentExprs}
1387      *
1388      *  Special treatment for arguments to primary constructor annotations.
1389      *  (...) is considered an argument only if it does not look like a formal
1390      *  parameter list, i.e. does not start with `( <annot>* <mod>* ident : `
1391      *  Furthermore, `()` is considered a annotation argument only if it comes first.
1392      */
1393     def parArgumentExprss(fn: Tree): Tree = {
1394       def isLegalAnnotArg: Boolean = {
1395         val lookahead = in.lookaheadScanner
1396         (lookahead.token == LPAREN) && {
1397           lookahead.nextToken()
1398           if (lookahead.token == RPAREN)
1399             !fn.isInstanceOf[Trees.Apply[_]] // allow one () as annotation argument
1400           else if (lookahead.token == IDENTIFIER) {
1401             lookahead.nextToken()
1402             lookahead.token != COLON
1403           }
1404           else canStartExpressionTokens.contains(lookahead.token)
1405         }
1406       }
1407       if (in.token == LPAREN && (!inClassConstrAnnots || isLegalAnnotArg))
1408         parArgumentExprss(Apply(fn, parArgumentExprs()))
1409       else fn
1410     }
1411 
1412     /** BlockExpr         ::= `{' BlockExprContents `}'
1413      *  BlockExprContents ::= CaseClauses | Block
1414      */
1415     def blockExpr(): Tree = atPos(in.offset) {
1416       inDefScopeBraces {
1417         if (in.token == CASE) Match(EmptyTree, caseClauses())
1418         else block()
1419       }
1420     }
1421 
1422     /** Block ::= BlockStatSeq
1423      *  @note  Return tree does not carry source position.
1424      */
1425     def block(): Tree = {
1426       val stats = blockStatSeq()
1427       def isExpr(stat: Tree) = !(stat.isDef || stat.isInstanceOf[Import])
1428       if (stats.nonEmpty && isExpr(stats.last)) Block(stats.init, stats.last)
1429       else Block(stats, EmptyTree)
1430     }
1431 
1432     /** Guard ::= if PostfixExpr
1433      */
1434     def guard(): Tree =
1435       if (in.token == IF) { in.nextToken(); postfixExpr() }
1436       else EmptyTree
1437 
1438     /** Enumerators ::= Generator {semi Enumerator | Guard}
1439      */
1440     def enumerators(): List[Tree] = generator() :: enumeratorsRest()
1441 
1442     def enumeratorsRest(): List[Tree] =
1443       if (isStatSep) { in.nextToken(); enumerator() :: enumeratorsRest() }
1444       else if (in.token == IF) guard() :: enumeratorsRest()
1445       else Nil
1446 
1447     /** Enumerator  ::=  Generator
1448      *                |  Guard
1449      *                |  Pattern1 `=' Expr
1450      */
1451     def enumerator(): Tree =
1452       if (in.token == IF) guard()
1453       else {
1454         val pat = pattern1()
1455         if (in.token == EQUALS) atPos(startOffset(pat), in.skipToken()) { GenAlias(pat, expr()) }
1456         else generatorRest(pat)
1457       }
1458 
1459     /** Generator   ::=  Pattern `<-' Expr
1460      */
1461     def generator(): Tree = generatorRest(pattern1())
1462 
1463     def generatorRest(pat: Tree) =
1464       atPos(startOffset(pat), accept(LARROW)) { GenFrom(pat, expr()) }
1465 
1466     /** ForExpr  ::= `for' (`(' Enumerators `)' | `{' Enumerators `}')
1467      *                {nl} [`yield'] Expr
1468      *            |  `for' Enumerators (`do' Expr | `yield' Expr)
1469      */
1470     def forExpr(): Tree = atPos(in.skipToken()) {
1471       var wrappedEnums = true
1472       val enums =
1473         if (in.token == LBRACE) inBraces(enumerators())
1474         else if (in.token == LPAREN) {
1475           val lparenOffset = in.skipToken()
1476           openParens.change(LPAREN, 1)
1477           val pats = patternsOpt()
1478           val pat =
1479             if (in.token == RPAREN || pats.length > 1) {
1480               wrappedEnums = false
1481               accept(RPAREN)
1482               openParens.change(LPAREN, -1)
1483               atPos(lparenOffset) { makeTupleOrParens(pats) } // note: alternatives `|' need to be weeded out by typer.
1484             }
1485             else pats.head
1486           val res = generatorRest(pat) :: enumeratorsRest()
1487           if (wrappedEnums) {
1488             accept(RPAREN)
1489             openParens.change(LPAREN, -1)
1490           }
1491           res
1492         } else {
1493           wrappedEnums = false
1494           enumerators()
1495         }
1496       newLinesOpt()
1497       if (in.token == YIELD) { in.nextToken(); ForYield(enums, expr()) }
1498       else if (in.token == DO) { in.nextToken(); ForDo(enums, expr()) }
1499       else {
1500         if (!wrappedEnums) syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(YieldOrDoExpectedInForComprehension())
1501         ForDo(enums, expr())
1502       }
1503     }
1504 
1505     /** CaseClauses ::= CaseClause {CaseClause}
1506     */
1507     def caseClauses(): List[CaseDef] = {
1508       val buf = new ListBuffer[CaseDef]
1509       buf += caseClause()
1510       while (in.token == CASE) buf += caseClause()
1511       buf.toList
1512     }
1513 
1514    /** CaseClause ::= case Pattern [Guard] `=>' Block
1515     */
1516     def caseClause(): CaseDef = atPos(in.offset) {
1517       accept(CASE)
1518       CaseDef(pattern(), guard(), atPos(accept(ARROW)) { block() })
1519     }
1520 
1521     /* -------- PATTERNS ------------------------------------------- */
1522 
1523     /**  Pattern           ::=  Pattern1 { `|' Pattern1 }
1524      */
1525     val pattern = () => {
1526       val pat = pattern1()
1527       if (isIdent(nme.raw.BAR))
1528         atPos(startOffset(pat)) { Alternative(pat :: patternAlts()) }
1529       else pat
1530     }
1531 
1532     def patternAlts(): List[Tree] =
1533       if (isIdent(nme.raw.BAR)) { in.nextToken(); pattern1() :: patternAlts() }
1534       else Nil
1535 
1536     /**  Pattern1          ::= PatVar Ascription
1537      *                      |  Pattern2
1538      */
1539     def pattern1(): Tree = {
1540       val p = pattern2()
1541       if (isVarPattern(p) && in.token == COLON) ascription(p, Location.InPattern)
1542       else p
1543     }
1544 
1545     /**  Pattern2    ::=  [id `@'] InfixPattern
1546      */
1547     val pattern2 = () => infixPattern() match {
1548       case p @ Ident(name) if in.token == AT =>
1549         val offset = in.skipToken()
1550 
1551         // compatibility for Scala2 `x @ _*` syntax
1552         infixPattern() match {
1553           case pt @ Ident(tpnme.WILDCARD_STAR) =>
1554             migrationWarningOrError("The syntax `x @ _*' is no longer supported; use `x : _*' instead", startOffset(p))
1555             atPos(startOffset(p), offset) { Typed(p, pt) }
1556           case p =>
1557             atPos(startOffset(p), offset) { Bind(name, p) }
1558         }
1559       case p @ Ident(tpnme.WILDCARD_STAR) =>
1560         // compatibility for Scala2 `_*` syntax
1561         migrationWarningOrError("The syntax `_*' is no longer supported; use `x : _*' instead", startOffset(p))
1562         atPos(startOffset(p)) { Typed(Ident(nme.WILDCARD), p) }
1563       case p =>
1564         p
1565     }
1566 
1567     /**  InfixPattern ::= SimplePattern {id [nl] SimplePattern}
1568      */
1569     def infixPattern(): Tree =
1570       infixOps(simplePattern(), canStartExpressionTokens, simplePattern, isOperator = in.name != nme.raw.BAR)
1571 
1572     /** SimplePattern    ::= PatVar
1573      *                    |  Literal
1574      *                    |  XmlPattern
1575      *                    |  `(' [Patterns] `)'
1576      *                    |  SimplePattern1 [TypeArgs] [ArgumentPatterns]
1577      *  SimplePattern1   ::= Path
1578      *                    |  SimplePattern1 `.' id
1579      *  PatVar           ::= id
1580      *                    |  `_'
1581      */
1582     val simplePattern = () => in.token match {
1583       case IDENTIFIER | BACKQUOTED_IDENT | THIS =>
1584         path(thisOK = true) match {
1585           case id @ Ident(nme.raw.MINUS) if isNumericLit => literal(startOffset(id))
1586           case t => simplePatternRest(t)
1587         }
1588       case USCORE =>
1589         val wildIndent = wildcardIdent()
1590 
1591         // compatibility for Scala2 `x @ _*` and `_*` syntax
1592         // `x: _*' is parsed in `ascription'
1593         if (isIdent(nme.raw.STAR)) {
1594           in.nextToken()
1595           if (in.token != RPAREN) syntaxError(SeqWildcardPatternPos(), wildIndent.pos)
1596           atPos(wildIndent.pos) { Ident(tpnme.WILDCARD_STAR) }
1597         } else wildIndent
1598       case LPAREN =>
1599         atPos(in.offset) { makeTupleOrParens(inParens(patternsOpt())) }
1600       case XMLSTART =>
1601         xmlLiteralPattern()
1602       case _ =>
1603         if (isLiteral) literal(inPattern = true)
1604         else {
1605           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(IllegalStartOfSimplePattern())
1606           errorTermTree
1607         }
1608     }
1609 
1610     def simplePatternRest(t: Tree): Tree = {
1611       var p = t
1612       if (in.token == LBRACKET)
1613         p = atPos(startOffset(t), in.offset) { TypeApply(p, typeArgs(namedOK = false, wildOK = false)) }
1614       if (in.token == LPAREN)
1615         p = atPos(startOffset(t), in.offset) { Apply(p, argumentPatterns()) }
1616       p
1617     }
1618 
1619     /** Patterns          ::=  Pattern [`,' Pattern]
1620      */
1621     def patterns() = commaSeparated(pattern)
1622 
1623     def patternsOpt(): List[Tree] =
1624       if (in.token == RPAREN) Nil else patterns()
1625 
1626 
1627     /** ArgumentPatterns  ::=  `(' [Patterns] `)'
1628      *                      |  `(' [Patterns `,'] Pattern2 `:' `_' `*' ')
1629      */
1630     def argumentPatterns(): List[Tree] =
1631       inParens(patternsOpt())
1632 
1633 /* -------- MODIFIERS and ANNOTATIONS ------------------------------------------- */
1634 
1635     private def modOfToken(tok: Int): Mod = tok match {
1636       case ABSTRACT  => Mod.Abstract()
1637       case FINAL     => Mod.Final()
1638       case IMPLICIT  => Mod.Implicit()
1639       case INLINE    => Mod.Inline()
1640       case LAZY      => Mod.Lazy()
1641       case OVERRIDE  => Mod.Override()
1642       case PRIVATE   => Mod.Private()
1643       case PROTECTED => Mod.Protected()
1644       case SEALED    => Mod.Sealed()
1645     }
1646 
1647     /** Drop `private' modifier when followed by a qualifier.
1648      *  Contract `abstract' and `override' to ABSOVERRIDE
1649      */
1650     private def normalize(mods: Modifiers): Modifiers =
1651       if ((mods is Private) && mods.hasPrivateWithin)
1652         normalize(mods &~ Private)
1653       else if (mods is AbstractAndOverride)
1654         normalize(addFlag(mods &~ (Abstract | Override), AbsOverride))
1655       else
1656         mods
1657 
1658     private def addModifier(mods: Modifiers): Modifiers = {
1659       val tok = in.token
1660       val mod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { modOfToken(tok) }
1661 
1662       if (mods is mod.flags) syntaxError(RepeatedModifier(mod.flags.toString))
1663       addMod(mods, mod)
1664     }
1665 
1666     private def compatible(flags1: FlagSet, flags2: FlagSet): Boolean = (
1667          flags1.isEmpty
1668       || flags2.isEmpty
1669       || flags1.isTermFlags && flags2.isTermFlags
1670       || flags1.isTypeFlags && flags2.isTypeFlags
1671     )
1672 
1673     def addFlag(mods: Modifiers, flag: FlagSet): Modifiers = {
1674       def getPrintableTypeFromFlagSet =
1675         Map(Trait -> "trait", Method -> "method", Mutable -> "variable").get(flag)
1676 
1677       if (compatible(mods.flags, flag)) mods | flag
1678       else {
1679         syntaxError(ModifiersNotAllowed(mods.flags, getPrintableTypeFromFlagSet))
1680         Modifiers(flag)
1681       }
1682     }
1683 
1684     /** Always add the syntactic `mod`, but check and conditionally add semantic `mod.flags`
1685      */
1686     def addMod(mods: Modifiers, mod: Mod): Modifiers =
1687       addFlag(mods, mod.flags).withAddedMod(mod)
1688 
1689     /** AccessQualifier ::= "[" (id | this) "]"
1690      */
1691     def accessQualifierOpt(mods: Modifiers): Modifiers =
1692       if (in.token == LBRACKET) {
1693         if ((mods is Local) || mods.hasPrivateWithin)
1694           syntaxError(DuplicatePrivateProtectedQualifier())
1695         inBrackets {
1696           if (in.token == THIS) { in.nextToken(); mods | Local }
1697           else mods.withPrivateWithin(ident().toTypeName)
1698         }
1699       } else mods
1700 
1701     /** {Annotation} {Modifier}
1702      *  Modifiers      ::= {Modifier}
1703      *  LocalModifiers ::= {LocalModifier}
1704      *  AccessModifier ::= (private | protected) [AccessQualifier]
1705      *  Modifier       ::= LocalModifier
1706      *                  |  AccessModifier
1707      *                  |  override
1708      *  LocalModifier  ::= abstract | final | sealed | implicit | lazy
1709      */
1710     def modifiers(allowed: BitSet = modifierTokens, start: Modifiers = Modifiers()): Modifiers = {
1711       @tailrec
1712       def loop(mods: Modifiers): Modifiers = {
1713         if (allowed contains in.token) {
1714           val isAccessMod = accessModifierTokens contains in.token
1715           val mods1 = addModifier(mods)
1716           loop(if (isAccessMod) accessQualifierOpt(mods1) else mods1)
1717         } else if (in.token == NEWLINE && (mods.hasFlags || mods.hasAnnotations)) {
1718           in.nextToken()
1719           loop(mods)
1720         } else {
1721           mods
1722         }
1723       }
1724       normalize(loop(start))
1725     }
1726 
1727     def implicitMods(): Modifiers =
1728       addMod(EmptyModifiers, atPos(accept(IMPLICIT)) { Mod.Implicit() })
1729 
1730     /** Wrap annotation or constructor in New(...).<init> */
1731     def wrapNew(tpt: Tree) = Select(New(tpt), nme.CONSTRUCTOR)
1732 
1733     /** Adjust start of annotation or constructor to position of preceding @ or new */
1734     def adjustStart(start: Offset)(tree: Tree): Tree = {
1735       val tree1 = tree match {
1736         case Apply(fn, args) => cpy.Apply(tree)(adjustStart(start)(fn), args)
1737         case Select(qual, name) => cpy.Select(tree)(adjustStart(start)(qual), name)
1738         case _ => tree
1739       }
1740       if (tree1.pos.exists && start < tree1.pos.start)
1741         tree1.withPos(tree1.pos.withStart(start))
1742       else tree1
1743     }
1744 
1745     /** Annotation        ::=  `@' SimpleType {ParArgumentExprs}
1746      */
1747     def annot() =
1748       adjustStart(accept(AT)) {
1749         if (in.token == INLINE) in.token = BACKQUOTED_IDENT // allow for now
1750         ensureApplied(parArgumentExprss(wrapNew(simpleType())))
1751       }
1752 
1753     def annotations(skipNewLines: Boolean = false): List[Tree] = {
1754       if (skipNewLines) newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(AT)
1755       if (in.token == AT) annot() :: annotations(skipNewLines)
1756       else Nil
1757     }
1758 
1759     def annotsAsMods(skipNewLines: Boolean = false): Modifiers =
1760       Modifiers() withAnnotations annotations(skipNewLines)
1761 
1762     def defAnnotsMods(allowed: BitSet): Modifiers =
1763       modifiers(allowed, annotsAsMods(skipNewLines = true))
1764 
1765  /* -------- PARAMETERS ------------------------------------------- */
1766 
1767     /** ClsTypeParamClause::=  `[' ClsTypeParam {`,' ClsTypeParam} `]'
1768      *  ClsTypeParam      ::=  {Annotation} [`+' | `-']
1769      *                         id [HkTypeParamClause] TypeParamBounds
1770      *
1771      *  DefTypeParamClause::=  `[' DefTypeParam {`,' DefTypeParam} `]'
1772      *  DefTypeParam      ::=  {Annotation} id [HkTypeParamClause] TypeParamBounds
1773      *
1774      *  TypTypeParamCaluse::=  `[' TypTypeParam {`,' TypTypeParam} `]'
1775      *  TypTypeParam      ::=  {Annotation} id [HkTypePamClause] TypeBounds
1776      *
1777      *  HkTypeParamClause ::=  `[' HkTypeParam {`,' HkTypeParam} `]'
1778      *  HkTypeParam       ::=  {Annotation} ['+' | `-'] (id [HkTypePamClause] | _') TypeBounds
1779      */
1780     def typeParamClause(ownerKind: ParamOwner.Value): List[TypeDef] = inBrackets {
1781       def typeParam(): TypeDef = {
1782         val isConcreteOwner = ownerKind == ParamOwner.Class || ownerKind == ParamOwner.Def
1783         val start = in.offset
1784         val mods = atPos(start) {
1785           annotsAsMods() | {
1786             if (ownerKind == ParamOwner.Class) Param | PrivateLocal
1787             else Param
1788           } | {
1789             if (ownerKind != ParamOwner.Def)
1790               if (isIdent(nme.raw.PLUS)) { in.nextToken(); Covariant }
1791               else if (isIdent(nme.raw.MINUS)) { in.nextToken(); Contravariant }
1792               else EmptyFlags
1793             else EmptyFlags
1794           }
1795         }
1796         atPos(start, nameStart) {
1797           val name =
1798             if (isConcreteOwner || in.token != USCORE) ident().toTypeName
1799             else {
1800               in.nextToken()
1801               WildcardParamName.fresh().toTypeName
1802             }
1803           val hkparams = typeParamClauseOpt(ParamOwner.TypeParam)
1804           val bounds =
1805             if (isConcreteOwner) typeParamBounds(name)
1806             else typeBounds()
1807           TypeDef(name, lambdaAbstract(hkparams, bounds)).withMods(mods)
1808         }
1809       }
1810       commaSeparated(() => typeParam())
1811     }
1812 
1813     def typeParamClauseOpt(ownerKind: ParamOwner.Value): List[TypeDef] =
1814       if (in.token == LBRACKET) typeParamClause(ownerKind) else Nil
1815 
1816     /** ClsParamClauses   ::=  {ClsParamClause} [[nl] `(' `implicit' ClsParams `)']
1817      *  ClsParamClause    ::=  [nl] `(' [ClsParams] ')'
1818      *  ClsParams         ::=  ClsParam {`' ClsParam}
1819      *  ClsParam          ::=  {Annotation} [{Modifier} (`val' | `var') | `inline'] Param
1820      *  DefParamClauses   ::=  {DefParamClause} [[nl] `(' `implicit' DefParams `)']
1821      *  DefParamClause    ::=  [nl] `(' [DefParams] ')'
1822      *  DefParams         ::=  DefParam {`,' DefParam}
1823      *  DefParam          ::=  {Annotation} [`inline'] Param
1824      *  Param             ::=  id `:' ParamType [`=' Expr]
1825      */
1826     def paramClauses(owner: Name, ofCaseClass: Boolean = false): List[List[ValDef]] = {
1827       var imods: Modifiers = EmptyModifiers
1828       var implicitOffset = -1 // use once
1829       var firstClauseOfCaseClass = ofCaseClass
1830       def param(): ValDef = {
1831         val start = in.offset
1832         var mods = annotsAsMods()
1833         if (owner.isTypeName) {
1834           mods = modifiers(start = mods) | ParamAccessor
1835           mods =
1836             atPos(start, in.offset) {
1837               if (in.token == VAL) {
1838                 val mod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { Mod.Val() }
1839                 mods.withAddedMod(mod)
1840               } else if (in.token == VAR) {
1841                 val mod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { Mod.Var() }
1842                 addMod(mods, mod)
1843               } else {
1844                 if (!(mods.flags &~ (ParamAccessor | Inline)).isEmpty)
1845                   syntaxError("`val' or `var' expected")
1846                 if (firstClauseOfCaseClass) mods else mods | PrivateLocal
1847               }
1848             }
1849         }
1850         else {
1851           if (in.token == INLINE) mods = addModifier(mods)
1852           mods = atPos(start) { mods | Param }
1853         }
1854         atPos(start, nameStart) {
1855           val name = ident()
1856           accept(COLON)
1857           if (in.token == ARROW && owner.isTypeName && !(mods is Local))
1858             syntaxError(VarValParametersMayNotBeCallByName(name, mods is Mutable))
1859           val tpt = paramType()
1860           val default =
1861             if (in.token == EQUALS) { in.nextToken(); expr() }
1862             else EmptyTree
1863           if (implicitOffset >= 0) {
1864             mods = mods.withPos(mods.pos.union(Position(implicitOffset, implicitOffset)))
1865             implicitOffset = -1
1866           }
1867           for (imod <- imods.mods) mods = addMod(mods, imod)
1868           ValDef(name, tpt, default).withMods(mods)
1869         }
1870       }
1871       def paramClause(): List[ValDef] = inParens {
1872         if (in.token == RPAREN) Nil
1873         else {
1874           if (in.token == IMPLICIT) {
1875             implicitOffset = in.offset
1876             imods = implicitMods()
1877           }
1878           commaSeparated(() => param())
1879         }
1880       }
1881       def clauses(): List[List[ValDef]] = {
1882         newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LPAREN)
1883         if (in.token == LPAREN)
1884           paramClause() :: {
1885             firstClauseOfCaseClass = false
1886             if (imods.hasFlags) Nil else clauses()
1887           }
1888         else Nil
1889       }
1890       val start = in.offset
1891       val result = clauses()
1892       if (owner == nme.CONSTRUCTOR && (result.isEmpty || (result.head take 1 exists (_.mods is Implicit)))) {
1893         in.token match {
1894           case LBRACKET   => syntaxError("no type parameters allowed here")
1895           case EOF        => incompleteInputError(AuxConstructorNeedsNonImplicitParameter())
1896           case _          => syntaxError(AuxConstructorNeedsNonImplicitParameter(), start)
1897         }
1898       }
1899       val listOfErrors = checkVarArgsRules(result)
1900       listOfErrors.foreach { vparam =>
1901         syntaxError(VarArgsParamMustComeLast(), vparam.tpt.pos)
1902       }
1903       result
1904     }
1905 
1906 /* -------- DEFS ------------------------------------------- */
1907 
1908     /** Import  ::= import ImportExpr {`,' ImportExpr}
1909      */
1910     def importClause(): List[Tree] = {
1911       val offset = accept(IMPORT)
1912       commaSeparated(importExpr) match {
1913         case t :: rest =>
1914           // The first import should start at the position of the keyword.
1915           t.withPos(t.pos.withStart(offset)) :: rest
1916         case nil => nil
1917       }
1918     }
1919 
1920     /**  ImportExpr ::= StableId `.' (id | `_' | ImportSelectors)
1921      */
1922     val importExpr = () => path(thisOK = false, handleImport) match {
1923       case imp: Import =>
1924         imp
1925       case sel @ Select(qual, name) =>
1926         val selector = atPos(pointOffset(sel)) { Ident(name) }
1927         cpy.Import(sel)(qual, selector :: Nil)
1928       case t =>
1929         accept(DOT)
1930         Import(t, Ident(nme.WILDCARD) :: Nil)
1931     }
1932 
1933     val handleImport = { tree: Tree =>
1934       if (in.token == USCORE) Import(tree, importSelector() :: Nil)
1935       else if (in.token == LBRACE) Import(tree, inBraces(importSelectors()))
1936       else tree
1937     }
1938 
1939     /** ImportSelectors ::= `{' {ImportSelector `,'} (ImportSelector | `_') `}'
1940      */
1941     def importSelectors(): List[Tree] = {
1942       val sel = importSelector()
1943       if (in.token == RBRACE) sel :: Nil
1944       else {
1945         sel :: {
1946           if (!isWildcardArg(sel) && in.token == COMMA) {
1947             in.nextToken()
1948             importSelectors()
1949           }
1950           else Nil
1951         }
1952       }
1953     }
1954    /** ImportSelector ::= id [`=>' id | `=>' `_']
1955      */
1956     def importSelector(): Tree = {
1957       val from = termIdentOrWildcard()
1958       if (from.name != nme.WILDCARD && in.token == ARROW)
1959         atPos(startOffset(from), in.skipToken()) {
1960           Thicket(from, termIdentOrWildcard())
1961         }
1962       else from
1963     }
1964 
1965     def posMods(start: Int, mods: Modifiers) = {
1966       val mods1 = atPos(start)(mods)
1967       in.nextToken()
1968       mods1
1969     }
1970 
1971     /** Def      ::= val PatDef
1972      *             | var VarDef
1973      *             | def DefDef
1974      *             | type {nl} TypeDcl
1975      *             | TmplDef
1976      *  Dcl      ::= val ValDcl
1977      *             | var ValDcl
1978      *             | def DefDcl
1979      *             | type {nl} TypeDcl
1980      *  EnumCase ::= `case' (EnumClassDef | ObjectDef)
1981      */
1982     def defOrDcl(start: Int, mods: Modifiers): Tree = in.token match {
1983       case VAL =>
1984         val mod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { Mod.Val() }
1985         val mods1 = mods.withAddedMod(mod)
1986         patDefOrDcl(start, mods1)
1987       case VAR =>
1988         val mod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { Mod.Var() }
1989         val mod1 = addMod(mods, mod)
1990         patDefOrDcl(start, mod1)
1991       case DEF =>
1992         defDefOrDcl(start, posMods(start, mods))
1993       case TYPE =>
1994         typeDefOrDcl(start, posMods(start, mods))
1995       case CASE =>
1996         enumCase(start, mods)
1997       case _ =>
1998         tmplDef(start, mods)
1999     }
2000 
2001     /** PatDef ::= Pattern2 {`,' Pattern2} [`:' Type] `=' Expr
2002      *  VarDef ::= PatDef | id {`,' id} `:' Type `=' `_'
2003      *  ValDcl ::= id {`,' id} `:' Type
2004      *  VarDcl ::= id {`,' id} `:' Type
2005      */
2006     def patDefOrDcl(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): Tree = atPos(start, nameStart) {
2007       val lhs = commaSeparated(pattern2)
2008       val tpt = typedOpt()
2009       val rhs =
2010         if (tpt.isEmpty || in.token == EQUALS) {
2011           accept(EQUALS)
2012           if (in.token == USCORE && !tpt.isEmpty && (mods is Mutable) &&
2013               (lhs.toList forall (_.isInstanceOf[Ident]))) {
2014             wildcardIdent()
2015           } else {
2016             expr()
2017           }
2018         } else EmptyTree
2019       lhs match {
2020         case (id @ Ident(name: TermName)) :: Nil => {
2021           ValDef(name, tpt, rhs).withMods(mods).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2022         } case _ =>
2023           PatDef(mods, lhs, tpt, rhs)
2024       }
2025     }
2026 
2027     private def checkVarArgsRules(vparamss: List[List[untpd.ValDef]]): List[untpd.ValDef] = {
2028       def isVarArgs(tpt: Trees.Tree[Untyped]): Boolean = tpt match {
2029         case PostfixOp(_, op) if op.name == tpnme.raw.STAR => true
2030         case _ => false
2031       }
2032 
2033       vparamss.flatMap { params =>
2034         if (params.nonEmpty) {
2035           params.init.filter(valDef => isVarArgs(valDef.tpt))
2036         } else List()
2037       }
2038     }
2039 
2040     /** DefDef ::= DefSig (`:' Type [`=' Expr] | "=" Expr)
2041      *           | this ParamClause ParamClauses `=' ConstrExpr
2042      *  DefDcl ::= DefSig `:' Type
2043      *  DefSig ::= id [DefTypeParamClause] ParamClauses
2044      */
