2045     def defDefOrDcl(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): Tree = atPos(start, nameStart) {
2046       def scala2ProcedureSyntax(resultTypeStr: String) = {
2047         val toInsert =
2048           if (in.token == LBRACE) s"$resultTypeStr ="
2049           else ": Unit "  // trailing space ensures that `def f()def g()` works.
2050         in.testScala2Mode(s"Procedure syntax no longer supported; `$toInsert' should be inserted here") && {
2051           patch(source, Position(in.lastOffset), toInsert)
2052           true
2053         }
2054       }
2055       if (in.token == THIS) {
2056         in.nextToken()
2057         val vparamss = paramClauses(nme.CONSTRUCTOR)
2058         if (in.isScala2Mode) newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2059         val rhs = {
2060           if (!(in.token == LBRACE && scala2ProcedureSyntax(""))) accept(EQUALS)
2061           atPos(in.offset) { constrExpr() }
2062         }
2063         makeConstructor(Nil, vparamss, rhs).withMods(mods)
2064       } else {
2065         val mods1 = addFlag(mods, Method)
2066         val name = ident()
2067         val tparams = typeParamClauseOpt(ParamOwner.Def)
2068         val vparamss = paramClauses(name)
2069         var tpt = fromWithinReturnType(typedOpt())
2070         if (in.isScala2Mode) newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2071         val rhs =
2072           if (in.token == EQUALS) {
2073             in.nextToken()
2074             expr()
2075           }
2076           else if (!tpt.isEmpty)
2077             EmptyTree
2078           else if (scala2ProcedureSyntax(": Unit")) {
2079             tpt = scalaUnit
2080             if (in.token == LBRACE) expr()
2081             else EmptyTree
2082           }
2083           else {
2084             if (!isExprIntro) syntaxError(MissingReturnType(), in.lastOffset)
2085             accept(EQUALS)
2086             expr()
2087           }
2088         DefDef(name, tparams, vparamss, tpt, rhs).withMods(mods1).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2089       }
2090     }
2091 
2092     /** ConstrExpr      ::=  SelfInvocation
2093      *                    |  ConstrBlock
2094      */
2095     def constrExpr(): Tree =
2096       if (in.token == LBRACE) constrBlock()
2097       else Block(selfInvocation() :: Nil, Literal(Constant(())))
2098 
2099     /** SelfInvocation  ::= this ArgumentExprs {ArgumentExprs}
2100      */
2101     def selfInvocation(): Tree =
2102       atPos(accept(THIS)) {
2103         newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2104         argumentExprss(Apply(Ident(nme.CONSTRUCTOR), argumentExprs()))
2105       }
2106 
2107     /** ConstrBlock    ::=  `{' SelfInvocation {semi BlockStat} `}'
2108      */
2109     def constrBlock(): Tree =
2110       atPos(in.skipToken()) {
2111         val stats = selfInvocation() :: {
2112           if (isStatSep) { in.nextToken(); blockStatSeq() }
2113           else Nil
2114         }
2115         accept(RBRACE)
2116         Block(stats, Literal(Constant(())))
2117       }
2118 
2119     /** TypeDef ::= type id [TypeParamClause] `=' Type
2120      *  TypeDcl ::= type id [TypeParamClause] TypeBounds
2121      */
2122     def typeDefOrDcl(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): Tree = {
2123       newLinesOpt()
2124       atPos(start, nameStart) {
2125         val name = ident().toTypeName
2126         val tparams = typeParamClauseOpt(ParamOwner.Type)
2127         in.token match {
2128           case EQUALS =>
2129             in.nextToken()
2130             TypeDef(name, lambdaAbstract(tparams, typ())).withMods(mods).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2131           case SUPERTYPE | SUBTYPE | SEMI | NEWLINE | NEWLINES | COMMA | RBRACE | EOF =>
2132             TypeDef(name, lambdaAbstract(tparams, typeBounds())).withMods(mods).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2133           case _ =>
2134             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(ExpectedTypeBoundOrEquals(in.token))
2135             EmptyTree
2136         }
2137       }
2138     }
2139 
2140     /** TmplDef ::=  ([`case' | `enum]'] class | trait) ClassDef
2141      *            |  [`case'] `object' ObjectDef
2142      *            |  `enum' EnumDef
2143      */
2144     def tmplDef(start: Int, mods: Modifiers): Tree = {
2145       in.token match {
2146         case TRAIT =>
2147           classDef(start, posMods(start, addFlag(mods, Trait)))
2148         case CLASS =>
2149           classDef(start, posMods(start, mods))
2150         case CASECLASS =>
2151           classDef(start, posMods(start, mods | Case))
2152         case OBJECT =>
2153           objectDef(start, posMods(start, mods | Module))
2154         case CASEOBJECT =>
2155           objectDef(start, posMods(start, mods | Case | Module))
2156         case ENUM =>
2157           val enumMod = atPos(in.skipToken()) { Mod.Enum() }
2158           if (in.token == CLASS) tmplDef(start, addMod(mods, enumMod))
2159           else enumDef(start, mods, enumMod)
2160         case _ =>
2161           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(ExpectedStartOfTopLevelDefinition())
2162           EmptyTree
2163       }
2164     }
2165 
2166     /** ClassDef ::= id ClassConstr TemplateOpt
2167      */
2168     def classDef(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): TypeDef = atPos(start, nameStart) {
2169       classDefRest(start, mods, ident().toTypeName)
2170     }
2171 
2172     def classDefRest(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers, name: TypeName): TypeDef = {
2173       val constr = classConstr(name, isCaseClass = mods is Case)
2174       val templ = templateOpt(constr)
2175       TypeDef(name, templ).withMods(mods).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2176     }
2177 
2178     /** ClassConstr ::= [ClsTypeParamClause] [ConstrMods] ClsParamClauses
2179      */
2180     def classConstr(owner: Name, isCaseClass: Boolean = false): DefDef = atPos(in.lastOffset) {
2181       val tparams = typeParamClauseOpt(ParamOwner.Class)
2182       val cmods = fromWithinClassConstr(constrModsOpt(owner))
2183       val vparamss = paramClauses(owner, isCaseClass)
2184       makeConstructor(tparams, vparamss).withMods(cmods)
2185     }
2186 
2187     /** ConstrMods        ::=  {Annotation} [AccessModifier]
2188      */
2189     def constrModsOpt(owner: Name): Modifiers =
2190       modifiers(accessModifierTokens, annotsAsMods())
2191 
2192     /** ObjectDef       ::= id TemplateOpt
2193      */
2194     def objectDef(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): ModuleDef = atPos(start, nameStart) {
2195       objectDefRest(start, mods, ident())
2196     }
2197 
2198     def objectDefRest(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers, name: TermName): ModuleDef = {
2199       val template = templateOpt(emptyConstructor)
2200       ModuleDef(name, template).withMods(mods).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2201     }
2202 
2203     /**  id ClassConstr [`extends' [ConstrApps]]
2204      *   [nl] { EnumCaseStats }
2205      */
2206     def enumDef(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers, enumMod: Mod): Thicket = {
2207       val point = nameStart
2208       val modName = ident()
2209       val clsName = modName.toTypeName
2210       val constr = classConstr(clsName)
2211       val parents =
2212         if (in.token == EXTENDS) {
2213           in.nextToken();
2214           newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2215           if (in.token == LBRACE) Nil else tokenSeparated(WITH, constrApp)
2216         }
2217         else Nil
2218       val clsDef = atPos(start, point) {
2219         TypeDef(clsName, Template(constr, parents, EmptyValDef, Nil))
2220           .withMods(addMod(mods, enumMod)).setComment(in.getDocComment(start))
2221       }
2222       newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2223       val modDef = atPos(in.offset) {
2224         val body = inBraces(enumCaseStats())
2225         ModuleDef(modName, Template(emptyConstructor, Nil, EmptyValDef, body))
2226           .withMods(mods)
2227       }
2228       Thicket(clsDef :: modDef :: Nil)
2229     }
2230 
2231     /** EnumCaseStats = EnumCaseStat {semi EnumCaseStat} */
2232     def enumCaseStats(): List[DefTree] = {
2233       val cases = new ListBuffer[DefTree] += enumCaseStat()
2234       var exitOnError = false
2235       while (!isStatSeqEnd && !exitOnError) {
2236         acceptStatSep()
2237         if (isCaseIntro)
2238           cases += enumCaseStat()
2239         else if (!isStatSep) {
2240           exitOnError = mustStartStat
2241           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete("illegal start of case")
2242         }
2243       }
2244       cases.toList
2245     }
2246 
2247     /** EnumCaseStat = {Annotation [nl]} {Modifier} EnumCase */
2248     def enumCaseStat(): DefTree =
2249       enumCase(in.offset, defAnnotsMods(modifierTokens))
2250 
2251     /** EnumCase = `case' (EnumClassDef | ObjectDef) */
2252     def enumCase(start: Offset, mods: Modifiers): DefTree = {
2253       val mods1 = mods.withAddedMod(atPos(in.offset)(Mod.EnumCase())) | Case
2254       accept(CASE)
2255 
2256       in.adjustSepRegions(ARROW)
2257         // Scanner thinks it is in a pattern match after seeing the `case`.
2258         // We need to get it out of that mode by telling it we are past the `=>`
2259 
2260       atPos(start, nameStart) {
2261         val id = termIdent()
2262         if (in.token == LBRACKET || in.token == LPAREN)
2263           classDefRest(start, mods1, id.name.toTypeName)
2264         else if (in.token == COMMA) {
2265           in.nextToken()
2266           val ids = commaSeparated(() => termIdent())
2267           PatDef(mods1, id :: ids, TypeTree(), EmptyTree)
2268         }
2269         else
2270           objectDefRest(start, mods1, id.name.asTermName)
2271       }
2272     }
2273 
2274 /* -------- TEMPLATES ------------------------------------------- */
2275 
2276     /** ConstrApp         ::=  SimpleType {ParArgumentExprs}
2277      */
2278     val constrApp = () => {
2279       val t = annotType()
2280       if (in.token == LPAREN) parArgumentExprss(wrapNew(t))
2281       else t
2282     }
2283 
2284     /** Template          ::=  ConstrApps [TemplateBody] | TemplateBody
2285      *  ConstrApps        ::=  ConstrApp {`with' ConstrApp}
2286      *
2287      *  @return  a pair consisting of the template, and a boolean which indicates
2288      *           whether the template misses a body (i.e. no {...} part).
2289      */
2290     def template(constr: DefDef): (Template, Boolean) = {
2291       newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2292       if (in.token == LBRACE) (templateBodyOpt(constr, Nil), false)
2293       else {
2294         val parents = tokenSeparated(WITH, constrApp)
2295         newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2296         val missingBody = in.token != LBRACE
2297         (templateBodyOpt(constr, parents), missingBody)
2298       }
2299     }
2300 
2301     /** TemplateOpt = [`extends' Template | TemplateBody]
2302      */
2303     def templateOpt(constr: DefDef): Template =
2304       if (in.token == EXTENDS) { in.nextToken(); template(constr)._1 }
2305       else {
2306         newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2307         if (in.token == LBRACE) template(constr)._1
2308         else Template(constr, Nil, EmptyValDef, Nil)
2309       }
2310 
2311     /** TemplateBody ::= [nl] `{' TemplateStatSeq `}'
2312      */
2313     def templateBodyOpt(constr: DefDef, parents: List[Tree]) = {
2314       val (self, stats) =
2315         if (in.token == LBRACE) templateBody() else (EmptyValDef, Nil)
2316       Template(constr, parents, self, stats)
2317     }
2318 
2319     def templateBody(): (ValDef, List[Tree]) = {
2320       val r = inDefScopeBraces { templateStatSeq() }
2321       if (in.token == WITH) {
2322         syntaxError(EarlyDefinitionsNotSupported())
2323         in.nextToken()
2324         template(emptyConstructor)
2325       }
2326       r
2327     }
2328 
2329 /* -------- STATSEQS ------------------------------------------- */
2330 
2331     /** Create a tree representing a packaging */
2332     def makePackaging(start: Int, pkg: Tree, stats: List[Tree]): PackageDef = pkg match {
2333       case x: RefTree => atPos(start, pointOffset(pkg))(PackageDef(x, stats))
2334     }
2335 
2336     /** Packaging ::= package QualId [nl] `{' TopStatSeq `}'
2337      */
2338     def packaging(start: Int): Tree = {
2339       val pkg = qualId()
2340       newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2341       val stats = inDefScopeBraces(topStatSeq())
2342       makePackaging(start, pkg, stats)
2343     }
2344 
2345     /** TopStatSeq ::= TopStat {semi TopStat}
2346      *  TopStat ::= Annotations Modifiers TmplDef
2347      *            | Packaging
2348      *            | package object objectDef
2349      *            | Import
2350      *            |
2351      */
2352     def topStatSeq(): List[Tree] = {
2353       val stats = new ListBuffer[Tree]
2354       while (!isStatSeqEnd) {
2355         setLastStatOffset()
2356         if (in.token == PACKAGE) {
2357           val start = in.skipToken()
2358           if (in.token == OBJECT)
2359             stats += objectDef(start, atPos(start, in.skipToken()) { Modifiers(Package) })
2360           else stats += packaging(start)
2361         }
2362         else if (in.token == IMPORT)
2363           stats ++= importClause()
2364         else if (in.token == AT || isTemplateIntro || isModifier)
2365           stats +++= tmplDef(in.offset, defAnnotsMods(modifierTokens))
2366         else if (!isStatSep) {
2367           if (in.token == CASE)
2368             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(OnlyCaseClassOrCaseObjectAllowed())
2369           else
2370             syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(ExpectedClassOrObjectDef())
2371           if (mustStartStat) // do parse all definitions even if they are probably local (i.e. a "}" has been forgotten)
2372             defOrDcl(in.offset, defAnnotsMods(modifierTokens))
2373         }
2374         acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd()
2375       }
2376       stats.toList
2377     }
2378 
2379     /** TemplateStatSeq  ::= [id [`:' Type] `=>'] TemplateStat {semi TemplateStat}
2380      *  TemplateStat     ::= Import
2381      *                     | Annotations Modifiers Def
2382      *                     | Annotations Modifiers Dcl
2383      *                     | EnumCaseStat
2384      *                     | Expr1
2385      *                     |
2386      */
2387     def templateStatSeq(): (ValDef, List[Tree]) = checkNoEscapingPlaceholders {
2388       var self: ValDef = EmptyValDef
2389       val stats = new ListBuffer[Tree]
2390       if (isExprIntro) {
2391         val first = expr1()
2392         if (in.token == ARROW) {
2393           first match {
2394             case Typed(tree @ This(EmptyTypeIdent), tpt) =>
2395               self = makeSelfDef(nme.WILDCARD, tpt).withPos(first.pos)
2396             case _ =>
2397               val ValDef(name, tpt, _) = convertToParam(first, expected = "self type clause")
2398               if (name != nme.ERROR)
2399                 self = makeSelfDef(name, tpt).withPos(first.pos)
2400           }
2401           in.nextToken()
2402         } else {
2403           stats += first
2404           acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd()
2405         }
2406       }
2407       var exitOnError = false
2408       while (!isStatSeqEnd && !exitOnError) {
2409         setLastStatOffset()
2410         if (in.token == IMPORT)
2411           stats ++= importClause()
2412         else if (isExprIntro)
2413           stats += expr1()
2414         else if (isDefIntro(modifierTokensOrCase))
2415           stats +++= defOrDcl(in.offset, defAnnotsMods(modifierTokens))
2416         else if (!isStatSep) {
2417           exitOnError = mustStartStat
2418           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete("illegal start of definition")
2419         }
2420         acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd()
2421       }
2422       (self, if (stats.isEmpty) List(EmptyTree) else stats.toList)
2423     }
2424 
2425     /** RefineStatSeq    ::= RefineStat {semi RefineStat}
2426      *  RefineStat       ::= Dcl
2427      *                     |
2428      *  (in reality we admit Defs and filter them out afterwards)
2429      */
2430     def refineStatSeq(): List[Tree] = {
2431       val stats = new ListBuffer[Tree]
2432       while (!isStatSeqEnd) {
2433         if (isDclIntro) {
2434           stats += defOrDcl(in.offset, Modifiers())
2435         } else if (!isStatSep) {
2436           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(
2437             "illegal start of declaration" +
2438             (if (inFunReturnType) " (possible cause: missing `=' in front of current method body)"
2439              else ""))
2440         }
2441         acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd()
2442       }
2443       stats.toList
2444     }
2445 
2446     def localDef(start: Int, implicitMods: Modifiers = EmptyModifiers): Tree = {
2447       var mods = defAnnotsMods(localModifierTokens)
2448       for (imod <- implicitMods.mods) mods = addMod(mods, imod)
2449       defOrDcl(start, mods)
2450     }
2451 
2452     /** BlockStatSeq ::= { BlockStat semi } [ResultExpr]
2453      *  BlockStat    ::= Import
2454      *                 | Annotations [implicit] [lazy] Def
2455      *                 | Annotations LocalModifiers TmplDef
2456      *                 | Expr1
2457      *                 |
2458      */
2459     def blockStatSeq(): List[Tree] = checkNoEscapingPlaceholders {
2460       val stats = new ListBuffer[Tree]
2461       var exitOnError = false
2462       while (!isStatSeqEnd && in.token != CASE && !exitOnError) {
2463         setLastStatOffset()
2464         if (in.token == IMPORT)
2465           stats ++= importClause()
2466         else if (isExprIntro)
2467           stats += expr(Location.InBlock)
2468         else if (isDefIntro(localModifierTokens))
2469           if (in.token == IMPLICIT) {
2470             val start = in.offset
2471             val imods = implicitMods()
2472             if (isBindingIntro) stats += implicitClosure(start, Location.InBlock, imods)
2473             else stats +++= localDef(start, imods)
2474           } else {
2475             stats +++= localDef(in.offset)
2476           }
2477         else if (!isStatSep && (in.token != CASE)) {
2478           exitOnError = mustStartStat
2479           syntaxErrorOrIncomplete(IllegalStartOfStatement(isModifier))
2480         }
2481         acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd(CASE)
2482       }
2483       stats.toList
2484     }
2485 
2486     /** CompilationUnit ::= {package QualId semi} TopStatSeq
2487      */
2488     def compilationUnit(): Tree = checkNoEscapingPlaceholders {
2489       def topstats(): List[Tree] = {
2490         val ts = new ListBuffer[Tree]
2491         while (in.token == SEMI) in.nextToken()
2492         val start = in.offset
2493         if (in.token == PACKAGE) {
2494           in.nextToken()
2495           if (in.token == OBJECT) {
2496             ts += objectDef(start, atPos(start, in.skipToken()) { Modifiers(Package) })
2497             if (in.token != EOF) {
2498               acceptStatSep()
2499               ts ++= topStatSeq()
2500             }
2501           } else {
2502             val pkg = qualId()
2503             newLineOptWhenFollowedBy(LBRACE)
2504             if (in.token == EOF)
2505               ts += makePackaging(start, pkg, List())
2506             else if (in.token == LBRACE) {
2507               ts += inDefScopeBraces(makePackaging(start, pkg, topStatSeq()))
2508               acceptStatSepUnlessAtEnd()
2509               ts ++= topStatSeq()
2510             }
2511             else {
2512               acceptStatSep()
2513               ts += makePackaging(start, pkg, topstats())
2514             }
2515           }
2516         }
2517         else
2518           ts ++= topStatSeq()
2519 
2520         ts.toList
2521       }
2522 
2523       topstats() match {
2524         case List(stat @ PackageDef(_, _)) => stat
2525         case Nil => EmptyTree  // without this case we'd get package defs without positions
2526         case stats => PackageDef(Ident(nme.EMPTY_PACKAGE), stats)
2527       }
2528     }
2529   }
2530 
2531 
2532   class OutlineParser(source: SourceFile)(implicit ctx: Context) extends Parser(source) {
2533 
2534     def skipBraces[T](body: T): T = {
2535       accept(LBRACE)
2536       var openBraces = 1
2537       while (in.token != EOF && openBraces > 0) {
2538         if (in.token == XMLSTART) xmlLiteral()
2539         else {
2540           if (in.token == LBRACE) openBraces += 1
2541           else if (in.token == RBRACE) openBraces -= 1
2542           in.nextToken()
2543         }
2544       }
2545       body
2546     }
2547 
2548     override def blockExpr(): Tree = skipBraces(EmptyTree)
2549 
2550     override def templateBody() = skipBraces((EmptyValDef, List(EmptyTree)))
2551   }
